Great food, and great customer service. I eat here regularly, and last week when they messed up my delivery order, they took responsibility right away and refunded me without any problem. It’s a great indication that they value their customers.

I never noticed this location until Covid kicked off and then I started to hit it up on the regular.  It is very popular and orders are through the app.  Now, once I got the hang of the app I was coasting but I really hate the app.  Not the best one for making subs in my book.  Once your order is placed, you go to the store to pick it up and the suggested time for being ready and pick up has been on point in my opinion, sometimes early.  Because of this I like to get there about 5 minutes beforehand.  The quality of the food is the same as when I would dine in and my only suggestion is you get your sauce on the side.

Mixed review. This was my second experience at SweetGreen, my fist at this location. I was impressed with how the long line moved quickly and the upkeep of the place. I came in with an order of 11 bowls (not ideal, but at least there wasn't a whole bunch of custom salads.) They made the bowls as quickly as they could which I was happy about. I give 3 stars because after I said 'thank you' and paid the cashier--who seemed to be the manager because of how she interacted with the other staff--she handed back my card, didn't even look at me, and went about her day. Unsure if they were upset that I had a large order which i should have placed online or was too busy to acknowledge me. I will give another chace in the future and review again.

No one answers the phone if you call with an issue. So no customer service during business hours. They are open till 10. You have the option to text for help but it’s automated. I did an app order and the guy at the register just handed me my bag as if it was my order. No confirmation. I got home to find that it’s not and I tried to call but no luck and text was useless. I rushed back because they’re about to close. 30 minutes wasted time. Will be looking at other places going forward because their app is not reliable.

We love Sweet Green. Our favorite salad is Guacamole Greens. It is awesome that Sweet Greens has both salad recipes and fresh, organic ingredients for you to chose from to build your own salad. This location actually shares space with the Anthony Bowen YMCA. So you can work out and pop over to grab a healthy meal and never have to step outside! Sweet Green is a wonderful alternative to traditional fast food. They offer clean, organic locally sourced food.

This sweetgreet is right next to the YMCA on W St. Definitely very convenient to get a quick meal after a post-work workout! The location does get a bit busy at times, but the team moves everyone along quickly.  The sweetgreen salads highlight what's in season so they are very fresh, and I really like the salad combinations. Though it's not one of the seasonal ones, my favorites are the Kale Caesar and Avocobbo. I tried their soup recently, and was less impressed. The butternut squash soup was runny and lacking flavor. They have delicious tart yogurt as well - very yummy with some chocolate chips and fresh fruit on top!
